Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update package lists and install Python tooling
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y \
        python3 \
        python3-venv \
        python3-pip \
        python3-setuptools \
        python3-wheel

    # Install pytest for the assessment framework
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # Ensure the expected home directory exists and is accessible
    mkdir -p /home/user
    chmod 0755 /home/user

    # Clean up apt caches to keep the image small
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Make sure “python3” and “pip3” are easily accessible
    export PATH="/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:$PATH"

%labels
    Author  "Container build script for perf_venv task"

%help
    This Apptainer image provides a minimal Ubuntu 22.04 environment with:
      • Python 3 and the “venv” module
      • pip and setuptools/wheel
      • pytest (required by the automated grader)

    The container purposefully does NOT create /home/user/perf_venv/
    so that the student can perform the required steps during assessment.